cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about monocular depth estimation using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of regression networks and multi-scale network structures, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of depth estimation for robotics applications, which suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) could be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for image processing, which could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
